1
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:06,040
She's blinking again.
-What?

2
00:00:06,760 --> 00:00:09,640
The neighbor downstairs. Who?
-She drags her leg. She blinks too.

3
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:11,720
Who would marry her?
-Come on, are you crazy?

4
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:14,960
The little one.
-So what?

5
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:16,760
So what? Honey, it's starting to worry me.

6
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:19,320
Enough. Come on, stop it. It'll pass.
-What if it doesn't pass?

7
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,640
You know I was looking
through the window, focused?

8
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:24,800
She can't sit for a minute in kindergarten.
-Because her teacher is boring.

9
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:26,480
Maybe she has attention issues?

10
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:29,160
Oh, really? And in ballet class
does she have rhythm and dance issues?

11
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:32,240
Come on, that's not funny.
Maybe we should give the girl Ritalin.

12
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:33,840
What? Seriously, did you hit your head?

13
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:36,360
I don't know where you grew up
but drugs aren't the answer.

14
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:38,440
It's not drugs, it's Ritalin, it's common.

15
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:39,880
It's drugs.
-It's medicine,

16
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:41,640
And there are people it can really help.

17
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:44,200
Like your mom.
-Parent involvement?

18
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:46,480
You started it.
-Everything's on you and you're clueless.

19
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:49,200
What an idiot.
-Maybe I need Ritalin too.

20
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,320
For you, Ritalin wouldn't help anymore.

21
00:00:58,120 --> 00:01:00,480
Look at me, look at me and...

22
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:15,200
So, what's up?
-All good, really good.

23
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:16,920
How are the parents? Did you talk to them?

24
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,920
Yeah, they're good. Having fun.

25
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:23,280
Well, of course! A trip around the world is amazing.

26
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:26,560
I've always dreamed of doing something like that.
-You can.

27
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:29,480
Just say "trip around the world",

28
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:31,080
I'm out the door, no packing.

29
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:34,600
But Pinchas is a different story.
-You don't like sailing.

30
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:37,400
Pinchas doesn't like anything.
-Not true.

31
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:39,760
I love the kids.
And I don't like being away

32
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,960
from my kids and grandkids for so long.

33
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:45,800
Nice.
-Nice, nice, but what about me?

34
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:48,800
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom.

35
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:51,640
Shabbat shalom, you already look worried.

36
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:54,920
Shabbat shalom, girls. Come here, come here, sweetie, come.

37
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:01,440
Einav, meet my oldest son, Shai.

38
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,600
Nice to meet you, Shai.
-The girls! This is his wife.

39
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:05,960
Sit down
Riki.
Sit down

40
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:07,600
Sit down
Sit down

41
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:12,480
Einav is the daughter of Yoel and Nili from the cafeteria.

42
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:15,440
They went on a long trip, so I invited her

43
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:18,320
to eat with us so she wouldn't sit home alone like a dog.

44
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:22,440
I know that from my son. You're in the same boat.

45
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:26,840
He's a great guy, lives alone in Tel Aviv...

46
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,520
Mom, can I have a minute in the kitchen?
-Why?

47
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:32,680
Pinchas, go change your shirt.
Why do I buy you shirts?

48
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:35,040
What's wrong with what I'm wearing? Shai bought it for me.

49
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:38,480
If it's for me, really no need.
-No, no. There is a need.

50
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:42,400
You should see
how my little one dresses, like a model.

51
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:44,480
Mom...
-Okay, I'm coming.

52
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:47,440
Excuse me, Einavi, my baby needs me.

53
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:54,360
Alright, I think I'll go change
my shirt. Otherwise, she won't leave me alone.

54
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,920
Are you a boy?
-Boy-

55
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:04,440
Welcome to the Rosen family Shabbat dinner.

56
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:09,200
With us, it's much worse.
-Wait. You just got here.

57
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,160
So what's the story?
-What story?

58
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,760
Mom, we didn't make you with a finger, you know.

59
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:21,240
I know, Shai, I'm giving her a name
-Ew.

60
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:25,480
Does she know she's coming to a blind date?
-What blind date?

61
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:28,760
She's coming to have a meal with us
and on the way, she'll meet Adam.

62
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:31,200
What's so terrible about that?
-So Adam doesn't know either.

63
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:33,640
He'll kill you.
-Don't mess with my head.

64
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:36,800
She's a lovely girl, she's a clinical psychologist,

65
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:39,880
she's an only child.
Do you know what her parents do?

66
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,440
What?
-Millions. That's what they do.

67
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:46,800
They own the biggest concrete factory in the country.

68
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:52,280
And when they die, God forbid, everything will go to her.

69
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:55,920
So excuse me
for worrying about my kids' future.

70
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,280
Wait, are they going to die?

71
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:01,160
They went on a cruise around the world.

72
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:05,960
What's that got to do with it?
-Ships sink sometimes...

73
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:07,360
God forbid?

74
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:21,640
It's hot today, huh?
-It's not the heat, it's the humidity.

75
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:25,600
Yeah, what's humidity? You take a fish,
you put it in the air, it swims.

76
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,440
Because of the humidity.
-Yeah, the humidity.

77
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:36,200
What, what, what are you doing?

78
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,400
At work?
-Let's say.

79
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:42,360
I have a master's degree, I'm a clinical psychologist.

80
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:43,520
Wow, cool.

81
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:50,400
Uh... clinical, that you have...
By the way, I had a debate like that

82
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:53,120
with my husband just now, in the car.
A kind of theoretical debate, of course,

83
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:57,040
about Ritalin. What do you say
clinically about Ritalin?

84
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,640
What's your opinion?
-It depends.

85
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:01,320
On what?
-Why, for whom, why.

86
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,240
For the girl, for the girl.
-Has she been tested?

87
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,880
No, no, you know, it's kind of theoretical,

88
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,880
hypothetical.
-Look, on one hand,

89
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:11,320
there are a lot of people and studies
that are very much in favor of this medication.

90
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,520
Wow...
-But on the other hand,

91
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:16,680
there are also those who are very against giving drugs to kids.

92
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:18,920
Wow...

93
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:27,760
Hello.
-Adam?

94
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:30,560
Ah, Dad, what's up? I'll be at your place in a few minutes.

95
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:33,320
Great, great. I just wanted to warn you, Adam.

96
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:37,280
Mom brought someone here,
and I think it's for matchmaking.

97
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,040
Why?
-Why?

98
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:40,920
You know how Mom is with her nonsense,

99
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,200
so I just wanted to give you a heads-up, be ready.

100
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:46,360
Okay. Thanks, Dad. Bye.
-Bye

101
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:50,480
Honey, here's a cancellation. I'll drop you off at home.

102
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,040
I'm starving.

103
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,000
I'll buy a pita on the way.

104
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:02,160
Either yes or no.
-Yeah, but at some point

105
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:04,800
you need to form an opinion. Right?
-That's the most important thing.

106
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:08,080
Yeah. It's either give Ritalin or not.

107
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:11,520
Right, but on the other hand, you don't have to form an opinion.

108
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:15,280
You can wonder, investigate, see
what the best way is for you and your daughter.

109
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:19,280
So not to give it to her?
-Or yes.

110
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:22,680
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

111
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:23,720
Shabbat Shalom.
-Bye

112
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,080
Hey there.
-Where's Mom? I'm starving.

113
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,400
Meet Einav.
-Hey there.

114
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:30,960
Are you friends?
-No, no. Riki invited her.

115
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:34,840
And you came?
-I'm the daughter of their friends,

116
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,800
Yoel and Billy.
-Ah.

117
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:40,160
You're Yoel and Nili's daughter from the kibbutz?
-Yeah.

118
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,560
Do you know them?
-Only from the stories.

119
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,200
Mom! Where is she? I'm starving.

120
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:47,800
She's with Shai in the kitchen.
-Come on, he probably already finished my food.

121
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:50,480
All the schnitzels.
How does he always manage to get to me?

122
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:53,480
So, what's up, Shani?
-Good, what about you?

123
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,920
Good, what about you?
-Great. What about you?

124
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,920
Great, what about you? What?

125
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,840
You know I'm a clinical psychologist?

126
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,280
Who?
Me.

127
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:06,720
Oh, what a coincidence. I had a classmate
in high school named Einav.

128
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:07,680
Really.
No way.

129
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:10,840
But she's good.
-Clinical.

130
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:17,440
You're lucky you didn't finish off all my schnitzels.

131
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,800
)Y
Len and
Nani
..and
the
why Marivanl
K'
son Y

132
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,280
Mom, how did you manage to drag
the millionaire's daughter from the kibbutz here?

133
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:28,720
How do you know about them?
-She tried to set me up with her after I got divorced.

134
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,600
Everyone knows you got divorced.
You don't need to shout it out.

135
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:35,400
Now she wants to set her up with Adam.
-Why set her up?

136
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:39,040
She's a lovely girl, she's a clinical psychologist,

137
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:41,120
and you know what her parents do?
-Millions.

138
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,280
From what?
-Insurance.

139
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,760
And she?
-Only child.

140
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:46,080
What will happen when her parents die?
-God willing.

141
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:48,040
God forbid.
-God forbid.

142
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:50,200
Who will inherit all the millions?
-She will.

143
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:53,120
Wow...
-Mom's doing her homework.

144
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:56,920
And you went and married a shoemaker's daughter.

145
00:07:57,040 --> 00:08:00,280
Tailor.
-Tailor, shoemaker, what's the difference?

146
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,280
Neither of them has a dime to their name.

147
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,640
And then Einav, my friend, told me she
doesn't want to and she'll wear what she wants,

148
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,480
so I told her: "Sorry, that's not acceptable to me."

149
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,840
In the end, look what came of her.

150
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,640
Anyway...
-I need to use the bathroom.

151
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,880
I'm in the middle of a story.

152
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:16,840
Fine, I know the ending,
you two argue and don't talk.

153
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:19,040
Come on, great, you ruined my punchline.
-Sorry.

154
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:20,680
Why...

155
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,400
A psychologist, huh?
-Clinical.

156
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,720
Yeah. So listen for a second,

157
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,760
I have a bit of a problem.
-No way.

158
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:33,480
Yeah. I mean, not me, my husband.

159
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:36,320
But it's about him. Right?
-If you want.

160
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:40,480
Every time we get into elevators
or crowded places

161
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:43,679
he immediately sticks to me
and starts touching me and kissing me.

162
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,600
He's your husband, he loves you.
-Yeah, but why in front of strangers?

163
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:49,720
Why in front of his kids?
No, he's kind of a perv in elevators.

164
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:50,800
And you know why that is?
-Why?

165
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,840
Because of his mom.
-Seriously?

166
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:57,480
Yeah. Riki. I mean, it's not
based on anything but that's how I feel.

167
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:00,200
What do you think?
-Look, it could be

168
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:02,000
that it really is related to his mom.
-I knew it.

169
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:05,120
On the other hand, it might not be.
-That...

170
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,520
Okay, she's coming, we'll talk about it later.

171
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:12,360
Anyway, I told her:
"Wear what I say and that's it."

172
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,160
Sit down, it's fine. I told him.
-What? To whom?

173
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,960
To Adam, that his mom is not normal.

174
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,800
Well, he already knew that. Right, Pinchas?

175
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:21,360
He knew that,
but he didn't know that there's a match waiting for him in the living room,

176
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:24,120
he didn't know that.
-What, is it a match?

177
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,760
Like a blind date?

178
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:28,400
Does she know she's being set up?
-No way!

179
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:32,000
Riki dragged her here with promises of homemade gourmet food.

180
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,760
Schnitzel and mashed potatoes is not gourmet, Pinchas.
-She's not normal.

181
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:37,120
We closed the circle.

182
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,400
What?
-I need to pee.

183
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,600
Oh, go ahead, go ahead. I’ll run to the living room,

184
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,200
to do some damage control.

185
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,160
Who were you talking about? You were definitely talking about me.

186
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:00,360
No way, Riki?
-No, we were talking about my friend,

187
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,240
the loser from high school.

188
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,680
Einav.

189
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:05,040
Not you, the whore.

190
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:09,080
Stop with this brothel. Einav, are you hungry?

191
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,160
We’re already sitting down to eat.
-Come on, come on,

192
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,160
you’re a psychologist, right? Because I have a dream

193
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,400
that keeps repeating itself.
-No way.

194
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:19,160
Yes, yes. I fall
into a tiny, tight black hole,

195
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:22,560
and a bunch of dwarfs come and start touching me all over.

196
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,720
What does that mean, you think?
-That you have a problem

197
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,400
with tight spaces. Right?
-No, that’s not true.

198
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:30,160
It means he’s messed up.
-Well, she’s not at work right now

199
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:33,480
and keep your perverted dreams to yourself.

200
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:34,800
Who’s perverted?
-Me.

201
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:36,000
Oh, of course.

202
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,680
Is the pervert the pianist?
-No, it’s the opera singer,

203
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:40,000
and no, it’s not.
-Are you sure?

204
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:42,800
Shai, come here for a sec.
-What..

205
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:43,760
Come here!

206
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,800
Coming, coming.

207
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:46,600
Wha_

208
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:51,880
Wait, wait, but I have another dream,
a really good one, too.

209
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,840
I dream I’m in an orphanage and I’m happy.

210
00:10:56,040 --> 00:11:00,160
What does that mean, you think?
-Laugh, laugh at your mom,

211
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:03,760
but not for a second would you survive without me.

212
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:06,200
You’d be left in the dark like a dog.

213
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:09,960
Riki, he has a wife.
-Why are you putting words in my mouth?

214
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,360
I said he’s alone like a dog,

215
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:14,800
I didn’t say you’re alone like a bitch.

216
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,560
Honey, it started small
and now she’s blinking all the time.

217
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:24,400
Maybe she has Tourette’s or something?
-Maybe it’s just tics?

218
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,440
I had those when I was a kid.
You’re not giving her drugs.

219
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:29,200
Aren’t we having this conversation?
-Okay, okay.

220
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,640
But since I met
that Einav, the psychologist.

221
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,760
What, the heiress?
-Yeah, Adam’s match.

222
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:38,040
And what, what did the wise one say?
-She said Ritalin is great,

223
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:40,520
that sometimes it can work wonders
for those who take it.

224
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,280
That’s what she said?
-Yeah, yeah.

225
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:45,520
She also said Ritalin is a type of drug,
that sometimes it can hold back

226
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:48,280
a child’s creativity.
-So she said that too,

227
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:50,440
on the other hand, she also contradicted herself.

228
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:53,640
Of course, she’s a psychologist.
What, is that what they learn in their first year?

229
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:56,320
So she’s a really smart psychologist.
-Probably.

230
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:58,280
Great, honey.
-And on the other hand?

231
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,880
Also.
-Honey?

232
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:04,320
What tics did you have when you were little?
-Forget it.

233
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,960
Come on, tell me. Come on, you and me.

234
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,560
I used to hug boys in the showers.

235
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,000
Einav.

236
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:16,440
I have a dream too.
-No way.

237
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:19,200
Yes, yes. I dream I’m in a hug

238
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:22,160
and when I wake up I really struggle to sleep.

239
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:25,160
So maybe you should see a doctor.

240
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:27,840
You’ve studied for so many weeks and you’re not a doctor?

241
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,800
Einav, don’t pay attention to what he says.

242
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,120
You don’t have any hug. It’s just psychosomatic.

243
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:37,440
Sounds more like psychonazimat.
-Funny, babe.

244
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:39,560
What’s this, who’s that? Who’s asthmatic?
-Me.

245
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:40,640
You, obviously.

246
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:44,320
Babe, wanna come with me for seven minutes
in heaven in your parents' room?

247
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:48,000
No, I married a 12-year-old girl.
Sure, babe. Let’s go.

248
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:52,040
Michali, you only have five minutes,
not seven. We’re eating soon.

249
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,160
Seriously, what about the food? I’m starving.

250
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,680
Where’s the groom?
-Shh!

251
00:12:57,280 --> 00:12:58,960
Who?
-Adam.

252
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,040
Adam?
-Shabbat sh...

253
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,440
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom.

254
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:07,120
Adamika.
-Where have you been? I was really worried.

255
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,320
Meet.
-Einav?

256
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,280
Adam?

257
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:12,120
What are you doing here?
-What are you doing here?

258
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,400
This is my parents' house.
-What, do you know each other?

259
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:19,360
Yeah, of course. How are you, Einav?

260
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:22,840
I’m great. And you?
-I’m great.

261
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,720
All good, good vibes-

262
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,400
So, are you listening?
-Yeah, come on.

263
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,920
So I talked to that Einav, the psychologist.
-The millionaire.

264
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:34,080
She’s a millionaire?
-Yeah. For real.

265
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:36,040
What, is there a saying, “millionaire for real”?

266
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,440
What? No, not the weight, the material.

267
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:43,120
What? Never mind. Listen.

268
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,640
So I talked to her, and she says
there’s definitely a chance,

269
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,880
fifty percent, that your elevator phobia
is because of your mom.

270
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,000
What?
-Every time you’re making out with me,

271
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:54,120
when we’re in the elevator or tight spaces,

272
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:55,480
it’s because of your mom.

273
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:59,840
What? What?

274
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:02,120
I don’t... I don’t really know
how to deal with what you just said.

275
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,920
Never mind. I’m just letting you know
there’s a maximum chance of 50 percent

276
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:07,400
that every time you touch me,
it’s like you’re touching your mom.

277
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:09,880
What?
-Yeah, but only in elevators, babe.

278
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:10,880
The rest of the time, it’s me.
-What?

279
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:11,800
Yeah.

280
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:14,520
Alright, so food?
-What?

281
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,480
What?

282
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,560
What are you doing to me?
-Why am I suddenly to blame?

283
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:22,480
What did you do to her?
-I didn’t do anything to her.

284
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,600
Oh, I saw the looks you two were giving each other.

285
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:28,840
He had a thing once, okay?

286
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,120
It happens.
-Do you know who she is?

287
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:34,240
The daughter of the concrete millionaires, she’s an only child,

288
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:36,400
when her parents die, God forbid,

289
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:39,760
with God’s help, all their money will go to her.

290
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:42,240
I know. Come on.
What, did they wipe out all my schnitzels?

291
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:45,920
What did I raise? Is this how you know me?

292
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:49,200
I saved some for you.
-What...

293
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:59,320
Tell me, what, are you normal? What did you say to my wife?

294
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,680
Shai, right? Can I talk to you alone for a sec?

295
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:04,040
Yeah, sure.
-What..

296
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,240
What’s this, what did she say to her?

297
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:11,200
She made up that I have some fear
of tight spaces.

298
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:14,200
Oh, that? That’s trivial, Michali. Forget it.

299
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:17,000
I actually think all his problems

300
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:20,320
started when he was born...
Mom wanted a girl, after all.

301
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:23,440
They should call her Tamar.
-So she called him "Hey Tamar."

302
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:27,400
Right. Itamar, you were always
wrapped in hugs and kisses.

303
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:29,800
He was as pretty as a girl until Adam was born...

304
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:31,920
Bo, enough already. Don't mess with my head. That's enough.

305
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,880
Honey, there are percentages saying it's this.

306
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,920
But what is she even doing with my wife?

307
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,640
What... she messed with her head.
-It's okay, turns out Adam messed with her first.

308
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:47,040
What's going on?
-Listen.

309
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:49,840
You seem the most sane here.
Now, as you already understand,

310
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:52,120
Adam and I have a bad history together.
-Yeah.

311
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:54,080
Since you know her better than I do,

312
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,840
How do I get out of here without offending Riki?

313
00:15:58,640 --> 00:16:00,240
No. No way.

314
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:01,800
Are you sure?

315
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:05,400
On the other hand,

316
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,560
No. No way.

317
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:11,800
She'll get offended.

318
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,200
That's nice.

319
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:31,680
Bo, why did you break up?

320
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:34,720
Tamari...
-That was a long time ago.

321
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,080
Who remembers?
-Thanks.

322
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:39,160
Drop it. It's been a few weeks.

323
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:42,360
There was.
-Seven-thirty. But who remembers?

324
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,040
Why didn't you tell me about her?

325
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,960
I actually told you guys,

326
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,040
about the one who took the test.

327
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:52,000
Yeah, but who remembers?

328
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:53,640
Do me a favor.

329
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:57,240
Alright, I'm out.

330
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:58,720
Riki, can I have a minute with you?

331
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,400
No way.

332
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:06,160
Look, Riki, I love you
but really, I have to go.

333
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:09,680
What test is he talking about?
-Pregnancy test.

334
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:12,599
I have a test I do
for guys I like.

335
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:15,200
I have a positive test from a friend,
I show it to them the morning after.

336
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,440
No way, I don't believe you.

337
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:19,160
I think that's a genius idea.

338
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:23,040
Is that what they taught you in university,
in clinical psychology?

339
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,520
No wonder you're alone, Einav.

340
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:32,560
No, you don't do that.
-What arrogance...

341
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:33,520
What did you do?

342
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,000
What do you think?

343
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,320
No, I said from the start that something's off with her.

344
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,480
Am I interrupting?

345
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:42,400
Yes.
-No, no, no.

346
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:43,840
What do you mean? We're just about to head out.

347
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:47,520
Because four people in this room is super cramped.

348
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,480
And I was already afraid Itamar
would start hugging me, touching me.

349
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:57,600
Shai, big problem. I...

350
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:06,800
Is this from Mom too?
-What did I do now?

351
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,800
Nothing. Shall we go to the table?

352
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,960
Yes.
-Yes. Kids, food.

353
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:14,760
Come on, come on kids.

354
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:18,800
Wait, sweetie. Come here, come here, come to Grandpa.

355
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:20,800
Why is your eye red?

356
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:22,920
Wait, wait, keep it open for a sec, honey.

357
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:27,040
Oh, you had a hair. That's it, go to the table.

358
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:30,080
How long has she been blinking like that?
-Uh...

359
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,560
Nothing, it just started now, just now.

360
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:33,080
Come to the table!

361
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,440
Look, I'm here just to
not offend your mom.

362
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:40,680
Here we go again with the arrogance.

363
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,320
Oh, you're not pretending now?
-Come on, really.

364
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:46,360
Because even if I told you
that you're a bitter single girl from Tel Aviv

365
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:49,480
with a predictable cat, you'd say
I'm just pretending. Right?

366
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,560
I'm bitter?
-You stopped getting married.

367
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:54,040
Who even wants to marry you
with your nonsense at home?

368
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:56,480
Who wants to marry you? Who talked about marriage?

369
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:59,160
Who even wants to touch you?
-Who knows what diseases you have?

370
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,800
Pseudo-intellectual.
-Primitive.

371
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:08,840
We're not waiting for them.
-How long is this taking?

372
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,280
I'm hungry.

373
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:14,280
Itamar Marshmallow, go call your little brother-
-Why me?

374
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:16,080
She asked me to, Itamar Griva.

375
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:18,520
Like two little kids, huh?

376
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,720
Yeah, but this time I have kids of your own.

377
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,160
Raz! Raz!

378
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:26,800
Raz! Raz!

379
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:31,520
Shluf Leaf, go call Uncle Adam to come.

380
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:37,480
So I understand that none of my kids

381
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:41,160
will marry a millionaire.
A concrete millionaire.

382
00:19:57,480 --> 00:20:00,440
Rivka, that's it, I can't take it anymore,
I'm really sorry.

383
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,680
I took a pill half an hour ago,
I took "Globin",

384
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:05,000
I'm hungry, I want it now. I want it now.

385
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:05,960
Here she comes back.

386
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:08,200
Oh, come on, Shluf Leaf, come here.

387
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,080
Where's Uncle Adam?

388
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:16,320
What did she say?

389
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,960
I don't know, I think
you should have sent someone else.

390
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,160
Is everything okay, honey?

391
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:30,560
I understood "iPhone."

392
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:33,360
Yeah, iPhone everyone... she loves to say iPhone.

393
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,680
It has nothing to do with anything. She says iPhone.
She uses it a lot, on the iPhone.

394
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:38,720
Sweetie, what's on your iPhone?

395
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:50,600
I'm sorry but I'll pass on the meal.

396
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:53,520
Say hi to the parents if they come back.

397
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,800
It was nice to see you again.

398
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,560
Come on
let them come

399
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:00,520
Hello.
-Come on

400
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:03,360
Come on..

401
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:07,280
You think? What about the food?

402
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:09,440
Go wash your hands.

403
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:19,640
They're Bradman.
-Thanks.

404
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:22,760
No, I should thank you.
-For what?

405
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:24,240
For the little one's blink.

406
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:27,040
Nonsense.
-No, really, thank you,

407
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:30,720
for not making me do the "I told you so" celebrations
in front of your mom.

408
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:34,600
As part of us trying
to provide the girls a better world

409
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,560
I hope we're doing
the right thing for them.

410
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:41,600
Yeah, but it won't help you.
-What do you mean?

411
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:45,840
Because when the girl grows up and sits on the couch
of her clinical psychologist

412
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:49,560
in the end, she'll blame you.
-That's true.

413
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:54,440
But on the other hand, you're not less to blame.

414
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:58,920
That's true, but on the third hand...

415
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:02,320
There's no third hand.
-That's true.

416
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:06,280
Where's the groom?

417
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:08,840
Adam! Oh... Shai!

418
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:12,920
Why, what would you do to me?

419
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,200
Yeah
come on

420
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:21,280
She said being a messy person is a great thing.

421
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:25,240
And if you give it to someone, they
can work wonders for that person.

422
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,680
Is that what she said?
-No, I messed up the text.

423
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:30,640
That's not what she said.

424
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:32,160
What?

425
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:38,480
She really drilled it into her head.
-Turns out Adam drilled it into her first.

426
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:40,560
He really got to her!

427
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:43,400
So, what's up with you?

428
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:52,120
You know I'm a clinical psychologist?

